. Prostomium with lateral incisions delimiting middle section, not reaching anterior end; prostomial glandular ridges absent; paired lateral dark pigment stripes in prostomium (
<figureCitation id="13392A2D834AFF92FADF4D3296832734" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,249,1093,1115]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,363,1066]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1435,359,1071]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Pavelius makranensis sp. nov. Holotype: (A) anterior end, lateral view; (B) thoracic, intermediate, and abdominal uncinigers, lateral view; (C) posterior end, ventral view. Paratype (SMF 24141): (D) anterior end, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262117/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="204">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
A). Buccal tentacles smooth. Four pairs of smooth cirriform branchiae arranged in one transverse row in segment III, not separated by median gap; branchiae with very densely arranged thick branchiophores, tapering distally; second outermost branchiae of transverse row originating from segment II, outermost branchiae of transverse row originating from segment III, innermost branchiae of transverse row originating from segment IV, second innermost branchiae of transverse row originating from segment V (
<figureCitation id="13392A2D834AFF92FC0B4DEE92252784" box="[955,1027,1736,1761]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="9.[151,249,1860,1882]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,1412,1831]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1435,1412,1838]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 7. ID cards: (A) Eclysippe yonaguniensis sp. nov. (B) Glyphanostomum bilabiatum sp. nov. (C) Pavelius makranensis sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262119/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="204">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
C). Segment II with small chaetae, resembling capillary notochaetae of following segments; chaetae of segment II emerging from notopodia like humps, located more ventrally than notopodia (
<figureCitation id="13392A2D834AFF92FD194C3694CA264C" box="[681,748,1808,1833]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,249,1093,1115]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,363,1066]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1435,359,1071]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Pavelius makranensis sp. nov. Holotype: (A) anterior end, lateral view; (B) thoracic, intermediate, and abdominal uncinigers, lateral view; (C) posterior end, ventral view. Paratype (SMF 24141): (D) anterior end, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262117/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="204">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
A). Notopodia with capillary chaetae (
<figureCitation id="13392A2D834AFF92FB2A4C3692FB264C" box="[1178,1245,1808,1833]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,249,1278,1300]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,267,1256]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1435,267,1257]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Pavelius makranensis sp. nov. SEM micrographs from SMF 24143: (A) capillary chaetae; (B) anterior end, dorsal view, arrow pointing to nephridial papilla; (C) thoracic uncini, lateral view; (D) thoracic uncini, frontal view; (E) abdominal neuropodium with uncini, posterior view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262118/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="204">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
A) from segment III, present in 15 chaetigers; first pair of notopodia smaller than following ones; first three pairs of notopodia slightly elevated dorsally above following notopodia; notopodia without cirri. Large nephridial papillae above notopodia of first unciniger (
<figureCitation id="13392A2D834AFF92FE6E4C5A940B26F0" box="[478,557,1916,1941]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,249,1093,1115]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,363,1066]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1435,359,1071]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Pavelius makranensis sp. nov. Holotype: (A) anterior end, lateral view; (B) thoracic, intermediate, and abdominal uncinigers, lateral view; (C) posterior end, ventral view. Paratype (SMF 24141): (D) anterior end, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262117/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="204">Figs. 5</figureCitation>
A, 6B). Neuropodial tori with uncini from segment VI, present in 12 thoracic uncinigers; tori without cirri. Continuous ventral shields conspicuous to thoracic unciniger 10, faint in thoracic unciniger 11. Two intermediate uncinigers (
<figureCitation id="13392A2D834AFF92FD124CE294CB26B8" box="[674,749,1988,2013]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,249,1093,1115]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,363,1066]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1435,359,1071]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Pavelius makranensis sp. nov. Holotype: (A) anterior end, lateral view; (B) thoracic, intermediate, and abdominal uncinigers, lateral view; (C) posterior end, ventral view. Paratype (SMF 24141): (D) anterior end, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262117/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="204">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
B). Sixteen abdominal uncinigers. Rudimentary notopodia present as small papillae in intermediate uncinigers and first abdominal unciniger (
<figureCitation id="13392A2D8345FF9DFBFB4BB192B621D5" box="[1099,1168,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,249,1093,1115]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,363,1066]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1435,359,1071]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Pavelius makranensis sp. nov. Holotype: (A) anterior end, lateral view; (B) thoracic, intermediate, and abdominal uncinigers, lateral view; (C) posterior end, ventral view. Paratype (SMF 24141): (D) anterior end, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262117/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="205">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
B), absent in remaining abdominal uncinigers. Pinnules without dorsal cirrus (
<figureCitation id="13392A2D8345FF9DFD444B9A951121B0" box="[756,823,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,249,1093,1115]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,363,1066]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1435,359,1071]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Pavelius makranensis sp. nov. Holotype: (A) anterior end, lateral view; (B) thoracic, intermediate, and abdominal uncinigers, lateral view; (C) posterior end, ventral view. Paratype (SMF 24141): (D) anterior end, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262117/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="205">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
C). Pygidium with terminal anus but without anal cirri. Thoracic uncini with unpaired tooth on top and paired median teeth over rostral tooth and basal prow, framed by small lateral teeth (
<figureCitation id="13392A2D8345FF9DFEC24A2297912078" box="[370,439,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,249,1278,1300]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,267,1256]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1435,267,1257]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Pavelius makranensis sp. nov. SEM micrographs from SMF 24143: (A) capillary chaetae; (B) anterior end, dorsal view, arrow pointing to nephridial papilla; (C) thoracic uncini, lateral view; (D) thoracic uncini, frontal view; (E) abdominal neuropodium with uncini, posterior view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262118/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="205">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
C, D). Abdominal uncini with about seven teeth over rostral tooth and basal prow (
<figureCitation id="13392A2D8345FF9DFADF4A2296802025" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,249,1278,1300]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,267,1256]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1435,267,1257]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Pavelius makranensis sp. nov. SEM micrographs from SMF 24143: (A) capillary chaetae; (B) anterior end, dorsal view, arrow pointing to nephridial papilla; (C) thoracic uncini, lateral view; (D) thoracic uncini, frontal view; (E) abdominal neuropodium with uncini, posterior view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262118/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="205">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
E). Tube made of dark grey clay.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF7D66208345FF9DFF274F6392D5251C" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262117/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="205" targetBox="[156,1431,363,1066]" targetPageId="8">
